We first need to calculate the Cash Flow to Debt Ratio using the formula:

  Cash Flow to Debt Ratio = (Net Cash Flow from Operating Activities) / (Total Liabilities)

In the provided balance sheet the only liabilities shown are the current liabilities. In this case, under “Total Current Liabilities” we have only "Taxes Payable" which is 727,140.68.

From the cash flow statement, the “Net Cash Flow from Operating Activities” is –17,417,367.15.

Thus, the calculation becomes:

  Ratio = (–17,417,367.15) / (727,140.68)

Performing the division:

  Ratio ≈ –23.95

The resulting Cash Flow to Debt Ratio is approximately –23.95.
